"Simon P., Knauth P., Tirado J.L., Plocharski J., Wieczorek W., Barnabé A., Tarascon J.-M., Masquelier C.","""Give energy to your study"": Students worldwide gather in Europe to design future Materials for Energy Storage and Conversion",2011,"Journal of Chemical Education","88","9",,"1203","1206",,,10.1021/ed900061h,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-80051592716&partnerID=40&md5=a48bc3f9d242b2f74d7d3e92e2e7f2a8","GRIMAT, Université de Toulouse, 31062 Toulouse, France; Laboratoire Chimie Provence, Université de Provence, 13397 Marseille, France; Departamento de Quimica Inorganica e Ingenieria Quimica, University of Cordoba, Campus de Rabanales, 14071 Cordoba, Spain; Faculty of Chemistry Technology, Warsaw University of Technology, 00-664 Warsaw, Poland; Université de Picardie Jules Verne, LRCS, 80039 Amiens, France","Simon, P., GRIMAT, Université de Toulouse, 31062 Toulouse, France; Knauth, P., Laboratoire Chimie Provence, Université de Provence, 13397 Marseille, France; Tirado, J.L., Departamento de Quimica Inorganica e Ingenieria Quimica, University of Cordoba, Campus de Rabanales, 14071 Cordoba, Spain; Plocharski, J., Faculty of Chemistry Technology, Warsaw University of Technology, 00-664 Warsaw, Poland; Wieczorek, W., Faculty of Chemistry Technology, Warsaw University of Technology, 00-664 Warsaw, Poland; Barnabé, A., GRIMAT, Université de Toulouse, 31062 Toulouse, France; Tarascon, J.-M., Université de Picardie Jules Verne, LRCS, 80039 Amiens, France; Masquelier, C., Université de Picardie Jules Verne, LRCS, 80039 Amiens, France","Global warming, finite fossil-fuel supplies, and urban pollution rapidly change the landscape of energy research worldwide and our training and education programs must change accordingly. Because of the natural intermittency of many renewable energy sources, there will be a far greater need for advanced electrical energy storage technology. Establishing highly diversified education programs that embrace worldwide scientists in this strategic area of science is of primary importance for bringing newly emerging concepts to fruition and securing our future. Five European universities pooled their efforts to create a specific, integrated, European Master's-level degree program, Materials for Energy Storage and Conversion, which offers high-level education while providing high mobility to students, as well as beneficial knowledge and exposure to relevant industrial settings. Copyright © 2011 American Chemical Society and Division of Chemical Education, Inc.","Continuing education; Electrochemistry; General public; Graduate education/research; Nanotechnology; Solid state chemistry; Upper-division undergraduate; X-ray crystallography",,,,,,,"Schlapbach, L., Zuttel, A., (2001) Nature, 414, pp. 353-358; Gratzel, M., (2005) Inorg. Chem., 44, pp. 6841-6851; Hoffert, M.I., Caldeira, K., Benford, G., Criswell, D.R., Green, C., Herzog, H., Jain, A.K., Wigley, T.M.L., (2002) Science, 298, pp. 981-987; Tarascon, J.-M., Armand, M., (2001) Nature, 414, pp. 359-367; Charlton, B.G., Andras, P., (2006) Med. Hypatheses, 66, pp. 869-873; Denofrio, L.A., Russell, B., Lopatto, D., Lu, Y., (2007) Science, 318, pp. 1872-1873; http://ec.europa.eu/education/programmes/mundus/programme/back_en.html, Web Site of the European Commission Erasmus Mundus Education Program (accessed Jun 2011)Materials for Energy Storage and Conversion, , http://www.u-picardie.fr/mundus_MESC, Web Site of the Master Degree Program (accessed Jun 2011); Ortiz, G., Hanzu, L., Djenizian, T., Lavela, P., Tirado, J.L., Knauth, P., (2009) Chem. Mater., 21, pp. 63-67; Di Vona, M.L., Sgreccia, E., Licoccia, S., Khadhraoui, M., Denoyel, R., Knauth, P., (2008) Chem. Mater., 20, pp. 4327-4334; Chmiola, J., Yushin, G., Gogotsi, Y., Portet, G., Simon, P., Taberna, P.L., (2006) Science, 313, pp. 1760-1763; Taberna, P.L., Mitra, S., Poizot, P., Simon, P., Tarascon, J.-M., (2006) Nat. Mater., 5, pp. 567-573; Miller, J.R., Simon, P., (2008) Science, 